Arizona police chief Terry Rozema spoke out on Wednesday to defend his officer after dashcam footage emerged showing him mounting a sidewalk in his speeding car .
Footage shows a cop car running into a suspect walking down a street in Marana, northwest of Tucon, Arizona, with a rifle .
Rozema was asked if Officer Michael Rapiejko was fortunate not to kill suspect Mario Valencia, 36, five times in the back as he ran away .